Nigerian gospel singer, Tope Alabi, on Saturday showered prayers on her daughter, Ayomiku, as the latter turned 24. Ayomiku, who is the singer’s first child, had announced her birthday in the early hours of Saturday. Sharing new photos of herself on her Instagram page, the 24-year-old wrote, “Happy Birthday Ayaba”. The veteran indigenous gospel artiste also shared pictures of her daughter on her Instagram page and showered praises and prayer on the celebrant. She wrote, “Thank you Lord Jesus for this day. Happy super birthday to my first 2nd me, first fruit, blood sister and daughter @the_ayomikualabi_ “I thank God for your life, your ministry, your beautiful heart. I pray as you celebrate another year today may the Lord bring you closer to him the more, guide you and make you fulfill destiny. “May all your good and godly heart desires be granted in Jesus’ mighty name, Amen. You are more than conqueror. Congratulations, my dear daughter.” The singer’s husband, Olusoji, also followed suit, as he also prayed for the celebration. He wrote, “Happy birthday my lovely daughter @the_ayomikualabi_ I thank God for your life and the grace of God upon your life. “I pray you will continually grow in the wisdom and knowledge of God. You will fulfill your destiny on earth in Jesus’ precious name. I love you dearly baby girl.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com